<item>
            <title>[FELIX-6127] escape nameHint for configuration listing </title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FELIX-6127</link>
                <project id="12310100" key="FELIX">Felix</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;There is a XSS vulnerability in configMgr where adding a html or script tag in log file name. Since this console is only accessible to admin, threat rating of this vulnerability is very low.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Steps to reproduce :&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;In /system/console/configMgr, find Apache Sling Logging Logger Configuration&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Edit one of the logs, e.g logs/auditlog.log&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Change to logs/auditlog.log&amp;lt;script&amp;gt;alert(&quot;xss&quot;)&amp;lt;/script&amp;gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Click Save and refresh&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Scroll to the configuration and see alert pop up injected&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Expected Behavior :&lt;/b&gt;&#160;Injected script should be escaped.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
